  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter was sent with a shipment of contributions from Jane Wigham to the Boston Anti-Slavery Bazaar. Andrew Paton refers to a new anti-slavery society that formed &quot;on acc[oun]t of the want of orthodoxy in our American friends.&quot; A black Presbyterian minister named Dr. Pennington helped the society to get started.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Included with this letter, is a list of articles sent by the Glasgow Female Anti-Slavery Society to the Boston Anti-Slavery Bazaar.</subfield>
